n Ng Shares His Photographic Vision: Shoot Now, Focus Later|last=Bonnington|first=Christina|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-04-20|language=en-US}}</ref> |- |2006||Aseem Agarwala |- |2007||Sergey Yekhanin |- |2007||Yan Liu |- |2007||Vincent Conitzer |- |2007||Benny Applebaum |- |2008||Sachin Katti |- |2008||Derek Hoiem |- |2008||Constantinos Daskalakis<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tornosnews.gr/en/greek-news/society/29538-greek-mit-professor-who-solved-%E2%80%9Cnash-puzzle%E2%80%9D-sad-over-brain-drain.html|title=Greek MIT professor who solved “Nash Puzzle” sad over brain drain {{!}} TornosNews.gr|work=TornosNews.GR|access-date=2018-04-20|language=el-GR}}</ref> |- |2009||Keith Noah Snavely |- |2009||Andre Platzer |- |2009||Haryadi S Gunawi |- |2009||[[Craig Gentry (computer scientist)|Craig Gentry]] |- |2010||Benjamin Snyder |- |2010||Bryan Parno |- |2011||David Steurer |- |2011||Aleksander Madry |- |2011||Seth Cooper<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/08/technology/u-of-washington-a-northwest-pipeline-to-silicon-valley.html|title=U. of Washington, a Northwest Pipeline to Silicon Valley|last=Wingfield|first=Nick|date=2012-07-07|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-04-20|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> |- |2012||Gergory Valiant |- |2012||Peter Hawkins |- |2012||Shyamnath Gollakota |- |2013||Shayan Oveis Gharan |- |2013||Sanjam Garg |- |2013||Grey Ballard |- |2014||[[Matei Zaharia|Matei Alexandru Zaharia]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eweek.com/enterprise-apps/how-apache-spark-is-transforming-big-data-processing-development|title=How Apache Spark Is Transforming Big Data Processing, Development|work=eWEEK|access-date=2018-04-20|language=en-US}}</ref> |- |2014||John C. Duchi |- |2014||John Criswell |- |2015||Aaron Sidford<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cs.cmu.edu/news/shun-receives-acm-doctoral-dissertation-award|title=Shun Receives ACM Doctoral Dissertation Award - Carnegie Mellon School of Computer Science|website=www.cs.cmu.edu}}</ref> |- |