[[Category:Individual graphs]] [[Category:Planar graphs]]
{{math-stub}}

In [[statistics]], '''iterated conditional modes''' is a [[deterministic algorithm]] for obtaining a configuration of a local maximum of the [[joint probability]] of a [[Markov random field]]. It does this by iteratively maximizing the probability of each variable [[conditional distribution|conditioned]] on the rest.
